<H1>Options</H1>

<P>The options dialog is separated into three panes. Click on the chooser at the top to display the desired option pane. Click <I>Save</I> to save the selected options and <I>Cancel</I> to preserve the current options.</P>


<H2><A NAME="image">Image</A></H2>

<P>The <I>Image</I> pane controls the image viewing and editing
options.

<CENTER><IMG SRC="options-image.jpg" WIDTH="496" HEIGHT="363"
ALT="Image Options in the Options Dialog"></CENTER>

<H3>Options</H3>

<P>Check the <I>Auto Open Images</I> box to automatically open
the last selected image in the image browser. Check the <I>Keep
Image Zoom</I> box to keep the current zoom when switching
images.

<H3>Editor</H3>

<P>Enter the name of the image editing program you wish to use,
or click on the <I>...</I> button to choose one with the
file chooser.

<H3>Gamma</H3>

<P>Drag the <I>Gamma</I> slider until the inside box disappears
inside the outer box. This will calibrate your display for
camera images.


<H2><A NAME="slideshow">Slideshow</A></H2>

<P>The <I>Slideshow</I> pane controls the slideshow options.

<CENTER><IMG SRC="options-slideshow.jpg" WIDTH="442" HEIGHT="363"
ALT="Slideshow Options in the Options Dialog"></CENTER>

<H3>Slide Delay</H3>

<P>Drag the <I>Slide Delay</I> slider to adjust the amount of
time each image will be displayed in a slideshow.

<H3>Options</H3>

<P>Check the <I>Start with First Slide</I> box to start the
slideshow with the first image in the album. Check the <I>Random
Order</I> box to display the images in a random order. Check the
<I>Repeat Slides</I> box to automatically restart the slideshow
when it reaches the last image. Check the <I>Show Comments</I> box to display the image property comments during the slideshow.</P>

<H3>Screen</H3>

<P>Choose the screen you would like to slideshow to use.</P>

<H3>Size</H3>

<P>Choose <I>Use Custom Size</I> to use a custom slideshow window size of <I>Use Screen Size</I> to use the full dimensions of the selected screen.</P>


<H2><A NAME="memorycard">Memory Card</A></H2>

<P>The <I>Memory Card</I> pane controls the camera memory card
options.

<CENTER><IMG SRC="options-memcard.jpg" WIDTH="503" HEIGHT="217"
ALT="Memory Card Options in the Options Dialog"></CENTER>

<H3>Directory</H3>

<P>Enter the directory which contains the memory card filesystem
or click on the <I>...</I> button to select one using the
directory chooser.

<H3>Options</H3>

<P>Check the <I>Mount card on use</I> button to automatically
mount and unmount the memory card when you open and close the
camera import dialog.


